      "writtenOn": "2026-06-03T21:50:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The plugin is normally built in-tree from Gerrit, so the Gerrit repository’s .bazelversion is the authoritative one for regular builds/tests.\n\nThe plugin-local .bazelversion is only useful for the occasional commands that I run from the plugin directory itself, for example regenerating the plugin MODULE.bazel.lock:\n\n```\n  bazelisk mod deps --lockfile_mode\u003dupdate\n```\n\nWithout a local .bazelversion, bazelisk falls back to its default/version selection outside the Gerrit workspace, which can regenerate the lock file with a different Bazel version than Gerrit uses.\n\nSo yes, if we keep this file, it should stay in sync with Gerrit’s .bazelversion. There is no automatic sync mechanism here; the practical alternatives are:\n\n* keep the plugin .bazelversion and update it whenever Gerrit’s .bazelversion changes, or\n* drop the plugin .bazelversion and require explicit version selection for standalone maintenance commands, e.g.\n\n```\n  USE_BAZELISK_VERSION\u003d9.1.0 bazelisk mod deps --lockfile_mode\u003dupdate\n```\n\nI kept the file to make plugin-local lockfile regeneration reproducible and less dependent on the developer’s bazelisk default.",
      "parentUuid": "327a78c0_d78911db",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 1,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 1,
        "endChar": 5
      },
